<div class="dablink">This article is about the US view of joint custody.  For the global view of joint custody, see <a href="Joint_custody" title="Joint custody">Joint custody</a>.</div>
<div class="dablink">This article is about the legal term.  For the American Dad! episode, see <a href="Joint_Custody_(American_Dad!)" title="Joint Custody (American Dad!)" class="mw-redirect">Joint Custody (American Dad!)</a>.</div>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main articles: <a href="Child_custody" title="Child custody">Child custody</a>, <a href="Shared_parenting" title="Shared parenting">Shared parenting</a>, and <a href="Best_interests" title="Best interests">Best interests</a></div>
<p><b>Joint custody</b> is a <a href="Court_order" title="Court order">court order</a> whereby <a href="Child_custody" title="Child custody">custody of a child</a> is awarded to both parties.<sup id="cite_ref-Arizona_State_Legislature_25-402_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Arizona_State_Legislature_25-402-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> In joint custody both parents are <a href="Custodial_parent" title="Custodial parent" class="mw-redirect">custodial parents</a> and neither parent is a <a href="Non-custodial_parent" title="Non-custodial parent" class="mw-redirect">non-custodial parent</a>, or, in other words, the child has two custodial parents.<sup id="cite_ref-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> In the United States, many states recognize two forms of joint custody, which include joint physical custody and joint legal custody.<sup id="cite_ref-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Georgia_Code_Section_19-9-6-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> In joint physical custody, the actual lodging and care of the child is shared according to a court-ordered custody schedule.<sup id="cite_ref-Oregon_Laws_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Oregon_Laws-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Kaplan_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kaplan-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> In joint legal custody, both parents share the ability to have access to their children's records, such as educational records, health records, and other records.<sup id="cite_ref-Marriage.2C_Divorce.2C_and_Children.27s_Adjustment_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Marriage.2C_Divorce.2C_and_Children.27s_Adjustment-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
